article.headline: Campbell 87, Kennesaw State 44
article.story: KENNESAW, Ga. -- Kyle Vejraska scored 18 points to lead Campbell to an 87-44 victory over Kennesaw State on Saturday, the Camels' largest margin of victory against a Division I opponent. The 43-point win also is Campbell's largest margin of victory against an Atlantic Sun Conference team and the most decisive road win since the Camels joined Division I in 1977-78. Leading 40-25 at halftime, Campbell (9-12, 6-6) outscored the Owls 31-7 to start the second half. The Camels were 12 of 22 from the 3-point line (54.4 percent) and Kennesaw State hit only 15 of 52 shots from the field (28.8 percent). The Owls (6-14, 2-9), who have lost 12 of their past 13 games, were 9 of 21 from the free-throw line (42.9 percent). Jonathan Rodriguez added 13 points and 15 rebounds and Amir Celestin had 11 points for Campbell. John Allison led Kennesaw State with 11 points.
